{
  "info": {
    "name": "Vess Device Service",
    "_postman_id": "vess-device-service-collection",
    "description": "Complete collection for the Vess Device Management Service API.\n\n**Setup:**\n1. Set `baseUrl` to your deployment URL.\n2. Set `accessToken` to a valid JWT from the auth-service (or import the auth collection and run Login first — the token is shared via the `accessToken` variable if both collections share an environment).\n3. After registering a device, the `deviceId` and `apiKey` variables are auto-populated for use in heartbeat and location requests.\n\n**Auth types used:**\n- `UserJWTAuthentication` — `Authorization: Bearer <accessToken>` for dashboard/user-facing endpoints.\n- `DeviceAPIKeyAuthentication` — `X-API-Key: <apiKey>` for device-originated endpoints (heartbeat, location).\n- Registration endpoints use a dashboard JWT decoded with `SECRET_KEY` (same Bearer token).",
    "schema": "https://schema.getpostman.com/json/collection/v2.1.0/collection.json"
  },
  "variable": [
    {
      "key": "baseUrl",
      "value": "http://vess-dev-alb-385758613.us-east-1.elb.amazonaws.com/device",
      "type": "string"
    },
    {
      "key": "accessToken",
      "value": "",
      "type": "string",
      "description": "JWT Bearer token from auth-service login. Used for all user-facing endpoints."
    },
    {
      "key": "deviceId",
      "value": "",
      "type": "string",
      "description": "Auto-populated after device registration."
    },
    {
      "key": "apiKey",
      "value": "",
      "type": "string",
      "description": "One-time API key returned on device registration. Used for heartbeat and location endpoints."
    },
    {
      "key": "registrationRequestId",
      "value": "",
      "type": "string",
      "description": "Auto-populated after creating a registration request."
    },
    {
      "key": "syncToken",
      "value": "",
      "type": "string",
      "description": "Sync link token extracted from sync_url after creating a registration request."
    }
  ],
  "item": [
    {
      "name": "Health",
      "item": [
        {
          "name": "Service Health",
          "request": {
            "method": "GET",
            "header": [],
            "url": {
              "raw": "{{baseUrl}}/health/",
              "host": ["{{baseUrl}}"],
              "path": ["health", ""]
            },
            "description": "Liveness probe. Returns service health including database and cache status."
          },
          "response": []
        },
        {
          "name": "System Health",
          "request": {
            "method": "GET",
            "header": [],
            "url": {
              "raw": "{{baseUrl}}/system/health/",
              "host": ["{{baseUrl}}"],
              "path": ["system", "health", ""]
            },
            "description": "Deep system health check across all dependencies. May return 503 if a dependency is degraded."
          },
          "response": []
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "name": "Devices",
      "item": [
        {
          "name": "List Devices",
          "request": {
            "auth": {
              "type": "bearer",
              "bearer": [{ "key": "token", "value": "{{accessToken}}", "type": "string" }]
            },
            "method": "GET",
            "header": [],
            "url": {
              "raw": "{{baseUrl}}/api/v1/devices/?status=&location=&created_after=&created_before=&ordering=-created_at&page=1&page_size=50",
              "host": ["{{baseUrl}}"],
              "path": ["api", "v1", "devices", ""],
              "query": [
                {
                  "key": "status",
                  "value": "",
                  "description": "Filter by status: ONLINE | OFFLINE | STALE | TESTING | DEGRADED"
                },
                {
                  "key": "location",
                  "value": "",
                  "description": "Case-insensitive substring match on location field"
                },
                {
                  "key": "created_after",
                  "value": "",
                  "description": "ISO 8601 datetime, e.g. 2025-01-01T00:00:00Z"
                },
                {
                  "key": "created_before",
                  "value": "",
                  "description": "ISO 8601 datetime"
                },
                {
                  "key": "ordering",
                  "value": "-created_at",
                  "description": "One of: created_at, -created_at, device_name, -device_name, status, -status"
                },
                {
                  "key": "page",
                  "value": "1"
                },
                {
                  "key": "page_size",
                  "value": "50",
                  "description": "Max 200"
                }
              ]
            },
            "description": "Returns a paginated list of all devices. Supports filtering by status, location, and date range."
          },
          "response": []
        },
        {
          "name": "Register Device",
          "event": [
            {
              "listen": "test",
              "script": {
                "exec": [
                  "if (pm.response.code === 201) {",
                  "    const body = pm.response.json();",
                  "    pm.collectionVariables.set('deviceId', body.device_id);",
                  "    pm.collectionVariables.set('apiKey', body.api_key);",
                  "    console.log('Device registered. device_id:', body.device_id);",
                  "    console.log('API Key (save this — it is shown only once):', body.api_key);",
                  "}"
                ],
                "type": "text/javascript"
              }
            }
          ],
          "request": {
            "auth": {
              "type": "bearer",
              "bearer": [{ "key": "token", "value": "{{accessToken}}", "type": "string" }]
            },
            "method": "POST",
            "header": [
              { "key": "Content-Type", "value": "application/json" }
            ],
            "body": {
              "mode": "raw",
              "raw": "{\n  \"device_id\": \"DEV-001\",\n  \"device_name\": \"Test Device Lagos\",\n  \"location\": \"Lagos Island, Lagos\",\n  \"latitude\": 6.4541,\n  \"longitude\": 3.3947,\n  \"metadata\": {\n    \"manufacturer\": \"Samsung\",\n    \"model\": \"Galaxy A54\",\n    \"android_version\": \"13\",\n    \"app_version\": \"1.0.0\"\n  }\n}"
            },
            "url": {
              "raw": "{{baseUrl}}/api/v1/devices/",
              "host": ["{{baseUrl}}"],
              "path": ["api", "v1", "devices", ""]
            },
            "description": "Register a new device. Returns a one-time `api_key` — store it immediately as it cannot be retrieved again. Coordinates must be within Nigeria bounds (lat 4–14°N, lng 3–15°E). The `deviceId` and `apiKey` variables are auto-saved."
          },
          "response": []
        },
        {
          "name": "Get Device Details",
          "request": {
            "auth": {
              "type": "bearer",
              "bearer": [{ "key": "token", "value": "{{accessToken}}", "type": "string" }]
            },
            "method": "GET",
            "header": [],
            "url": {
              "raw": "{{baseUrl}}/api/v1/devices/{{deviceId}}/",
              "host": ["{{baseUrl}}"],
              "path": ["api", "v1", "devices", "{{deviceId}}", ""]
            },
            "description": "Retrieve full device details including health metrics, recent test executions (from test-service), and aggregated statistics."
          },
          "response": []
        },
        {
          "name": "Update Device",
          "request": {
            "auth": {
              "type": "bearer",
              "bearer": [{ "key": "token", "value": "{{accessToken}}", "type": "string" }]
            },
            "method": "PUT",
            "header": [
              { "key": "Content-Type", "value": "application/json" }
            ],
            "body": {
              "mode": "raw",
              "raw": "{\n  \"device_name\": \"Updated Device Name\",\n  \"location\": \"Abuja, FCT\",\n  \"latitude\": 9.0579,\n  \"longitude\": 7.4951,\n  \"metadata\": {\n    \"app_version\": \"1.1.0\"\n  }\n}"
            },
            "url": {
              "raw": "{{baseUrl}}/api/v1/devices/{{deviceId}}/",
              "host": ["{{baseUrl}}"],
              "path": ["api", "v1", "devices", "{{deviceId}}", ""]
            },
            "description": "Update device configuration or metadata. Requires `admin` or `operator` role in the JWT. All fields are optional — only provided fields are updated. Metadata is merged (not replaced)."
          },
          "response": []
        },
        {
          "name": "Deregister Device",
          "request": {
            "auth": {
              "type": "bearer",
              "bearer": [{ "key": "token", "value": "{{accessToken}}", "type": "string" }]
            },
            "method": "DELETE",
            "header": [
              { "key": "Content-Type", "value": "application/json" }
            ],
            "body": {
              "mode": "raw",
              "raw": "{\n  \"reason\": \"Device decommissioned\"\n}"
            },
            "url": {
              "raw": "{{baseUrl}}/api/v1/devices/{{deviceId}}/",
              "host": ["{{baseUrl}}"],
              "path": ["api", "v1", "devices", "{{deviceId}}", ""]
            },
            "description": "Soft-deregisters a device by setting `is_active=false` and recording `deregistered_at`. Requires `admin` role in the JWT. Publishes a `device.deregistered` event."
          },
          "response": []
        },
        {
          "name": "Search Devices",
          "request": {
            "auth": {
              "type": "bearer",
              "bearer": [{ "key": "token", "value": "{{accessToken}}", "type": "string" }]
            },
            "method": "GET",
            "header": [],
            "url": {
              "raw": "{{baseUrl}}/api/v1/devices/search/?q=Lagos",
              "host": ["{{baseUrl}}"],
              "path": ["api", "v1", "devices", "search", ""],
              "query": [
                {
                  "key": "q",
                  "value": "Lagos",
                  "description": "Required. Searches across device_id, device_name, and location fields."
                }
              ]
            },
            "description": "Full-text search across `device_id`, `device_name`, and `location`. Returns up to 50 results ordered by `created_at` descending."
          },
          "response": []
        },
        {
          "name": "Find Nearby Devices",
          "request": {
            "auth": {
              "type": "bearer",
              "bearer": [{ "key": "token", "value": "{{accessToken}}", "type": "string" }]
            },
            "method": "GET",
            "header": [],
            "url": {
              "raw": "{{baseUrl}}/api/v1/devices/nearby/?lat=6.4541&lng=3.3947&radius_km=50",
              "host": ["{{baseUrl}}"],
              "path": ["api", "v1", "devices", "nearby", ""],
              "query": [
                {
                  "key": "lat",
                  "value": "6.4541",
                  "description": "Required. Centre latitude."
                },
                {
                  "key": "lng",
                  "value": "3.3947",
                  "description": "Required. Centre longitude."
                },
                {
                  "key": "radius_km",
                  "value": "50",
                  "description": "Optional. Search radius in kilometres. Defaults to 50."
                }
              ]
            },
            "description": "Geospatial search using the Haversine formula. Returns all devices within `radius_km` of the given coordinates, sorted by distance ascending. Each result includes a `distance_km` field."
          },
          "response": []
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "name": "Device Operations",
      "item": [
        {
          "name": "Send Heartbeat",
          "request": {
            "method": "POST",
            "header": [
              { "key": "Content-Type", "value": "application/json" },
              { "key": "X-API-Key", "value": "{{apiKey}}", "description": "Device API key returned at registration" }
            ],
            "body": {
              "mode": "raw",
              "raw": "{\n  \"battery_level\": 85,\n  \"storage_available_mb\": 2048,\n  \"network_type\": \"4G\",\n  \"signal_strength\": -75,\n  \"latitude\": 6.4541,\n  \"longitude\": 3.3947,\n  \"app_version\": \"1.0.0\"\n}"
            },
            "url": {
              "raw": "{{baseUrl}}/api/v1/devices/{{deviceId}}/heartbeat/",
              "host": ["{{baseUrl}}"],
              "path": ["api", "v1", "devices", "{{deviceId}}", "heartbeat", ""]
            },
            "description": "Device-originated endpoint. Authenticated via `X-API-Key` header (not Bearer JWT).\n\nUpdates device status based on health metrics:\n- `battery_level < 15` → DEGRADED (low_battery)\n- `signal_strength < -100` → DEGRADED (low_signal)\n- `storage_available_mb < 500` → DEGRADED (low_storage)\n- `network_type == '2G'` → DEGRADED (poor_network)\n- Otherwise → ONLINE\n- TESTING status is preserved regardless of metrics.\n\nReturns `pending_commands` count and `next_heartbeat_in_ms`."
          },
          "response": []
        },
        {
          "name": "Update Location",
          "request": {
            "method": "PUT",
            "header": [
              { "key": "Content-Type", "value": "application/json" },
              { "key": "X-API-Key", "value": "{{apiKey}}", "description": "Device API key returned at registration" }
            ],
            "body": {
              "mode": "raw",
              "raw": "{\n  \"latitude\": 6.5244,\n  \"longitude\": 3.3792,\n  \"location\": \"Victoria Island, Lagos\"\n}"
            },
            "url": {
              "raw": "{{baseUrl}}/api/v1/devices/{{deviceId}}/location/",
              "host": ["{{baseUrl}}"],
              "path": ["api", "v1", "devices", "{{deviceId}}", "location", ""]
            },
            "description": "Device-originated endpoint. Authenticated via `X-API-Key` header. A device can only update its own location. Coordinates must be within Nigeria bounds."
          },
          "response": []
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "name": "Registration Requests",
      "item": [
        {
          "name": "Create Registration Request",
          "event": [
            {
              "listen": "test",
              "script": {
                "exec": [
                  "if (pm.response.code === 201) {",
                  "    const body = pm.response.json();",
                  "    pm.collectionVariables.set('registrationRequestId', body.registration_id);",
                  "    console.log('Registration request ID:', body.registration_id);",
                  "",
                  "    // Extract the token from the sync_url path segment",
                  "    if (body.sync_url) {",
                  "        const parts = body.sync_url.split('/').filter(Boolean);",
                  "        const token = parts[parts.length - 1];",
                  "        pm.collectionVariables.set('syncToken', token);",
                  "        console.log('Sync token saved:', token);",
                  "    }",
                  "}"
                ],
                "type": "text/javascript"
              }
            }
          ],
          "request": {
            "auth": {
              "type": "bearer",
              "bearer": [{ "key": "token", "value": "{{accessToken}}", "type": "string" }]
            },
            "method": "POST",
            "header": [
              { "key": "Content-Type", "value": "application/json" }
            ],
            "body": {
              "mode": "raw",
              "raw": "{\n  \"phone_number\": \"+2348012345678\",\n  \"reference\": \"FIELD-AGENT-001\"\n}"
            },
            "url": {
              "raw": "{{baseUrl}}/api/v1/registration/requests/",
              "host": ["{{baseUrl}}"],
              "path": ["api", "v1", "registration", "requests", ""]
            },
            "description": "Create a single device registration request. Generates a one-time sync URL sent via SMS to the field agent's phone number. The `registrationRequestId` and `syncToken` variables are auto-saved from the response."
          },
          "response": []
        },
        {
          "name": "Create Bulk Registration Requests",
          "request": {
            "auth": {
              "type": "bearer",
              "bearer": [{ "key": "token", "value": "{{accessToken}}", "type": "string" }]
            },
            "method": "POST",
            "header": [
              { "key": "Content-Type", "value": "application/json" }
            ],
            "body": {
              "mode": "raw",
              "raw": "{\n  \"registrations\": [\n    {\n      \"phone_number\": \"+2348012345678\",\n      \"reference\": \"AGENT-001\"\n    },\n    {\n      \"phone_number\": \"+2348087654321\",\n      \"reference\": \"AGENT-002\"\n    },\n    {\n      \"phone_number\": \"+2348055556666\",\n      \"reference\": \"AGENT-003\"\n    }\n  ]\n}"
            },
            "url": {
              "raw": "{{baseUrl}}/api/v1/registration/requests/bulk/",
              "host": ["{{baseUrl}}"],
              "path": ["api", "v1", "registration", "requests", "bulk", ""]
            },
            "description": "Create up to 500 registration requests in a single call. Each entry gets its own sync URL and SMS. Returns `count` and `results` array."
          },
          "response": []
        },
        {
          "name": "Get Registration Request",
          "request": {
            "auth": {
              "type": "bearer",
              "bearer": [{ "key": "token", "value": "{{accessToken}}", "type": "string" }]
            },
            "method": "GET",
            "header": [],
            "url": {
              "raw": "{{baseUrl}}/api/v1/registration/requests/{{registrationRequestId}}/",
              "host": ["{{baseUrl}}"],
              "path": ["api", "v1", "registration", "requests", "{{registrationRequestId}}", ""]
            },
            "description": "Retrieve details of a specific registration request. Only the user who created the request can access it."
          },
          "response": []
        },
        {
          "name": "Revoke Registration Request",
          "request": {
            "auth": {
              "type": "bearer",
              "bearer": [{ "key": "token", "value": "{{accessToken}}", "type": "string" }]
            },
            "method": "POST",
            "header": [],
            "body": {
              "mode": "raw",
              "raw": ""
            },
            "url": {
              "raw": "{{baseUrl}}/api/v1/registration/requests/{{registrationRequestId}}/revoke/",
              "host": ["{{baseUrl}}"],
              "path": ["api", "v1", "registration", "requests", "{{registrationRequestId}}", "revoke", ""]
            },
            "description": "Revoke a pending registration sync link by marking it as expired. Returns 409 if the request has already been approved."
          },
          "response": []
        },
        {
          "name": "Regenerate Sync Link",
          "event": [
            {
              "listen": "test",
              "script": {
                "exec": [
                  "if (pm.response.code === 200) {",
                  "    const body = pm.response.json();",
                  "    if (body.sync_url) {",
                  "        const parts = body.sync_url.split('/').filter(Boolean);",
                  "        const token = parts[parts.length - 1];",
                  "        pm.collectionVariables.set('syncToken', token);",
                  "        console.log('New sync token saved:', token);",
                  "    }",
                  "}"
                ],
                "type": "text/javascript"
              }
            }
          ],
          "request": {
            "auth": {
              "type": "bearer",
              "bearer": [{ "key": "token", "value": "{{accessToken}}", "type": "string" }]
            },
            "method": "POST",
            "header": [],
            "body": {
              "mode": "raw",
              "raw": ""
            },
            "url": {
              "raw": "{{baseUrl}}/api/v1/registration/requests/{{registrationRequestId}}/regenerate/",
              "host": ["{{baseUrl}}"],
              "path": ["api", "v1", "registration", "requests", "{{registrationRequestId}}", "regenerate", ""]
            },
            "description": "Generate a new sync link for an existing registration request (e.g. if the previous link expired). Resets status to `pending` and issues a new SMS. Returns 409 if already approved. The new `syncToken` is auto-saved."
          },
          "response": []
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "name": "Sync Link (Device-side)",
      "item": [
        {
          "name": "Validate Sync URL",
          "request": {
            "method": "GET",
            "header": [],
            "url": {
              "raw": "{{baseUrl}}/api/v1/registration/sync/{{syncToken}}/",
              "host": ["{{baseUrl}}"],
              "path": ["api", "v1", "registration", "sync", "{{syncToken}}", ""]
            },
            "description": "Called by the device app when the field agent opens the sync URL. Validates the token and returns registration metadata (phone number, reference, expiry). Returns 404 for invalid tokens, 410 for used or expired ones.\n\nRate-limited (validate throttle)."
          },
          "response": []
        },
        {
          "name": "Complete Sync (Approve Registration)",
          "event": [
            {
              "listen": "test",
              "script": {
                "exec": [
                  "if (pm.response.code === 200) {",
                  "    const body = pm.response.json();",
                  "    pm.collectionVariables.set('deviceId', body.device_id);",
                  "    pm.collectionVariables.set('apiKey', body.api_key);",
                  "    console.log('Device approved via sync. device_id:', body.device_id);",
                  "    console.log('API Key (save this — shown only once):', body.api_key);",
                  "}"
                ],
                "type": "text/javascript"
              }
            }
          ],
          "request": {
            "method": "POST",
            "header": [
              { "key": "Content-Type", "value": "application/json" }
            ],
            "body": {
              "mode": "raw",
              "raw": "{\n  \"device_id\": \"DEV-SYNC-001\",\n  \"device_name\": \"Field Device Kano\",\n  \"location\": \"Kano Municipal, Kano\",\n  \"latitude\": 12.0022,\n  \"longitude\": 8.5920,\n  \"metadata\": {\n    \"manufacturer\": \"Tecno\",\n    \"model\": \"Spark 10\",\n    \"android_version\": \"12\",\n    \"app_version\": \"1.0.0\"\n  }\n}"
            },
            "url": {
              "raw": "{{baseUrl}}/api/v1/registration/sync/{{syncToken}}/",
              "host": ["{{baseUrl}}"],
              "path": ["api", "v1", "registration", "sync", "{{syncToken}}", ""]
            },
            "description": "Called by the device app to complete registration via the sync link. Atomically creates the device record, marks the registration request as `approved`, and returns a one-time `api_key`. The sync link is consumed and cannot be reused.\n\nRate-limited (complete throttle). `deviceId` and `apiKey` are auto-saved."
          },
          "response": []
        }
      ]
    }
  ]
}
